# Styling Rules

## Design Direction

Industrial-refined aesthetic. Dark tones, metallic accents, bold signature accent color. No pastel palettes, no gradients-on-white, nothing that reads as "tech startup."

### Typography
- Display/Headings: bold condensed or slab-serif (Barlow Condensed, Bebas Neue, Archivo Black). All-caps for section headers.
- Body: clean sans-serif (Source Sans 3, DM Sans, Outfit).
- Import via Google Fonts. Never Inter, Arial, or system defaults.

### Colors (extend in tailwind.config.ts)
- Background: `#1a1a1a` / `#0f0f0f`
- Surface: `#2a2a2a`
- Accent: one bold color (burnt orange, safety yellow, oil-slick teal)
- Text: `#e5e5e5` body, white headings
- Muted: medium gray

## No Inline CSS — Ever

Zero `style={{}}` in JSX. Use Tailwind classes or component `.styles.css` files.

## Tailwind — Ready Classes Only

- Use the built-in spacing scale (`p-4`, `gap-6`, `max-w-xl`). **Never** arbitrary values like `p-[13px]` or `w-[247px]`.
- Extend the theme in `tailwind.config.ts` for project tokens. No hex values in class strings.
- Group classes: layout → sizing → spacing → typography → colors → effects → states.
- Use `cn()` (clsx + twMerge) for conditional classes. Never string-concatenate.

## Component-Scoped CSS

Only when Tailwind can't express the style (complex keyframes, pseudo-elements). File: `ComponentName.styles.css` in the component folder. This is the exception, not the norm.

## Flexbox First

- Default to `flex` for all layouts. `flex-col` for stacking, `flex-row flex-wrap` for horizontal.
- Use `gap-*` for spacing between children.
- **Grid is the last resort.** Only for genuine 2D layouts flex can't handle.

## No Margin

- Avoid `m-*`, `mt-*`, `mb-*`, `mx-*`, `my-*`.
- Use `gap-*` on the parent flex container.
- Use `p-*` for internal spacing.
- If margin is truly unavoidable, add a comment explaining why.

```tsx
// ✅ Parent owns spacing
<div className="flex flex-col gap-6">
  <Heading>Our Services</Heading>
  <ServiceList />
</div>

// ❌ Children manage spacing
<div className="flex flex-col">
  <Heading className="mb-6">Our Services</Heading>
  <ServiceList className="mb-8" />
</div>
```

## Responsive — Mobile First

- Build mobile layout first, enhance with `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`.
- Common: `flex-col md:flex-row`, `w-full md:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3`, `text-2xl md:text-4xl`.
- Test at **320px minimum**. No horizontal scrolling on any viewport.
- Touch targets: **44×44px** minimum on mobile.
